<subSubSection id="C3036541FFC38B1A5E8FFE6420D2FC93" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA636CAFFC38B1A5E8FFE64224EFDB8" blockId="48.[189,303,502,528]" box="[189,303,502,528]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<heading id="D0EE81A6FFC38B1A5E8FFE64224EFDB8" bold="true" box="[189,303,502,528]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFC38B1A5E8FFE64224EFDB8" bold="true" box="[189,303,502,528]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA636CAFFC38B1A5E8FFDB620A8FD2D" blockId="48.[189,1399,548,645]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
The single card mounted specimen used by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF884B3BFFC38B1A5C8DFDB7203BFD96" author="Hesse J. C." box="[703,858,548,575]" firstAuthor="Hesse" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the South African Museum" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="475 - 536" part="25" refId="ref30885" refString="Hesse J. C. 1929. Some new species of Curculionidae from South Africa and South West Africa. Annals of the South African Museum 25: 475 - 536." title="Some new species of Curculionidae from South Africa and South West Africa" type="journal article" year="1929">
<collectingRegion id="49DDF828FFC38B1A5C8DFDB72064FD97" box="[703,773,549,575]" country="Germany" name="Hessen" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Hesse</collectingRegion>
(1929)
</bibRefCitation>
for the description of 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFC38B1A5A53FDB62616FD96" authorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Haran &amp; Benoit &amp; Procheş &amp; Kergoat" baseAuthorityYear="2022" box="[1121,1399,548,574]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Derelomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rhodesianus">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFC38B1A5A53FDB62616FD96" box="[1121,1399,548,574]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Derelomus rhodesianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<collectingRegion id="49DDF828FFC38B1A5E8FFDDA2262FDCA" box="[189,259,584,610]" country="Germany" name="Hessen" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Hesse</collectingRegion>
was located in the collection housed at SAMC. This specimen bears a red type label, it was identified as the 
<typeStatus id="54A28868FFC38B1A5F4CFDF82284FD2C" box="[382,485,618,644]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">holotype</typeStatus>
for this species and labelled accordingly.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA636CAFFC38B1A5E8FFD3E222EFD6E" blockId="48.[189,335,684,710]" box="[189,335,684,710]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<heading id="D0EE81A6FFC38B1A5E8FFD3E222EFD6E" bold="true" box="[189,335,684,710]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFC38B1A5E8FFD3E222EFD6E" bold="true" box="[189,335,684,710]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Life history</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA636CAFFC38B1A5E8FFD4820D2FC93" blockId="48.[188,1399,730,827]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
This species was collected in large numbers on 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFC38B1A5CD0FD4820C9FD5C" box="[738,936,730,756]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ebenaceae" genus="Euclea" isUncertain="true" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="crispa">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFC38B1A5CD0FD482052FD5C" box="[738,819,730,756]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Euclea</emphasis>
cf. 
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFC38B1A5D6DFD4920C9FD5C" box="[863,936,731,756]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">crispa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Adults were observed on the branches, near the flower buds before blooming. The single record on flowers of 
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFC38B1A5A17FD6F27ACFCBF" box="[1061,1229,765,791]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Lonchocarpus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B96DEAD8FFC38B1A5A17FD6F27ACFCBF" box="[1061,1229,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Lonchocarpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C194D49FFC38B1A5AEDFD6F2631FCB0" baseAuthorityName="Franz &amp; Valente" baseAuthorityYear="2005" box="[1247,1360,765,792]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Fabaceae</taxonomicName>
) is probably accidental. Adults were collected from July to October.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
